ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://map-india.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Website-cover-images-new-2026-04-22T092946.933.png
CATEGORIES:Workshops,MAP,CBD
DTSTAMP:20260505T125252Z
DESCRIPTION:A session that moves from gallery to garden.\nBegin with a guided walkthrough of Paper Gardens \, before stepping into the Living Botanical installation with its gardener\, Kush Sethi. Drawing connections between the artworks and the plants around you\, Kush will guide you through observing species\, forms\, compositions\, and the quiet details of plant anatomy.\nThe session then transitions into a hands-on gardening workshop\, slow-paced and unhurried\, where you will practise the art of potting and composing. A gentle introduction to becoming a plant parent.\nYour completed piece is yours to take home.
DTEND:20260509T103000Z
DTSTART:20260509T090000Z
SUMMARY:Plant Parenting 101
UID:1259@map-india.org
URL:https://map-india.org/map-events/plant-parenting-101/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://map-india.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/DSC00963-scaled-e1778247442455.jpg
CATEGORIES:Guided Walk,MAP,CBD
DTSTAMP:20260508T133944Z
DESCRIPTION:Join us for an immersive and accessible experience specially designed for people with visual disabilities at MAP’s Living Botanical followed by an interactive workshop with artist Mohit Mahato.\n\nThe session will begin with a guided walkthrough of the garden\, where participants will experience and engage with a variety of plants through touch\, smell\, observation\, and discussion. Following the walkthrough\, Mohit will lead a workshop exploring plants in greater depth\, including their behaviour\, medicinal value\, the types of soil they grow in\, the climates they thrive in\, and which parts of the plants are considered most useful or valuable.\n\nMohit will also share insights into his artistic practice and how nature influences his work. Drawing from his experience as an artist\, he will speak about how he uses different parts of trees and plants within his art-making process\, creating connections between ecology\, material\, texture\, and artistic expression.\n\nThis session invites participants with visual disabilities to connect with nature not only through sensory exploration and learning\, but also through creativity and artistic imagination.
DTEND:20260524T113000Z
DTSTART:20260524T093000Z
SUMMARY:Scent\, Soil\, and Art: An Immersive Experience
UID:1272@map-india.org
URL:https://map-india.org/map-events/scent-soil-and-art-an-immersive-experience/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://map-india.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/nature-art-workshop-iisc-2024-scaled-e1775708092836.jpg
CATEGORIES:Workshops,MAP,CBD
DTSTAMP:20260507T054443Z
DESCRIPTION:Image Credit: Dr Sambita Modak\nThrough this workshop\, we will connect the audience to the impacts of climate change on ecosystems and how these impacts affect the series of socio-economic linkages around us. The session will focus on three key lenses: biodiversity\, food and water systems\, and social fabric\, connecting these through storytelling and data visualisation. \n\nThrough art explorations\, we will examine themes such as climate grief\, climate injustice\, and the interconnection between them and ecosystems.
DTEND:20260509T140000Z
DTSTART:20260509T103000Z
SUMMARY:Climate Canvases
UID:1249@map-india.org
URL:https://map-india.org/map-events/climate-canvases/
